Among the prepared novel cephalosporin derivatives related to S-3578, a series of 7beta-[2-(5-amino-1,2,4-thiadiazol-3-yl)-2-(Z)-ethoxyiminoacetamido]-3-[1-(aminoa lkyl)-1H-pyrazolo[4,3-b]pyridinium-4-yl]methyl-3-cephem-4-carboxylate showed potent activity against both MRSA and Pseudomonas aeruginosa, and displayed good water solubility.